Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about text-to-speech synthesis, which falls under the intersection of computation and language. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper deals with audio synthesis. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper proposes a new approach to reduce latencies in TTS systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possibility as the paper uses neural methods for TTS synthesis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely as the paper focuses on a specific application of AI (TTS) rather than AI in general.
